I‚Äôve been here for lunch and dinner. Google restricts my review to one meal (at least for photos and menu items) but I‚Äôd love to share my experiences of both. My latest visit was for lunch. This is one of the most underrated lunch experiences in Atlanta. The atmosphere is light, airy, casual but elevated/sophisticated. Menu seems unassuming but has some absolute knockouts. Service was also just really enjoyable; I‚Äôm not much of a conversationalist but had Caroline at the bar and ended up having one of the best restaurant chats in recent memory, and was guided through the menu for an awesome selection of the omelette, sticky toffee pudding, and coffee. Dinners are more intimate, and a little hard to get a reservation so it‚Äôs been tough for my schedule. Unsure how a group reservation would go but can vouch for solo trips and dates, or close 1:1 catch ups. Despite the reservation struggles, I appreciate the smaller seating capacity and streamlined menu. I suppose I‚Äôd like more small bite options to pair with the wine because I always end up getting the Jam√≥n Ib√©rico and would like more meats, but that‚Äôs knit pick. I‚Äôll end with a confirmation that the book store element is not a gimmick and not aesthetics only - the curation is so well done. I‚Äôve gotten 5 books as gifts and 2 for myself. Really appreciate this spot. Atlanta could use more spaces like this that execute on the actual food experience as well as they do in the creativity and vibe.
Sherlin was the sweetest! Food was also amazing. Must try!
Great experience here! Major shout out to Sherlin for her exceptional service! Would 100% come back.

I just sat at the drive-through speaker for over 10 minutes without anyone talking to me. I drove up to the window and took me about three minutes to get someone's attention and then they acted like it was my fault that they weren't doing their job. do not recommend this Dunkin' Donuts.
Good food good fun in a secure environment.

Having tried thoroughly enjoyed our omakase experiences at Mujo and Hiyakawa we have been trying to find other similar experiences in Atlanta. I am happy to report that Brush's omakase did not disappoint. The service was outstanding. Both the servers and the chef spent generous amounts of time talking with us and making sure we had everything we needed/wanted. We did the 16 course menu and it was the perfect amount a food and I would say it is a better value when compared to Mujo or Hiyakawa. I would say the atmosphere sits in between those two. Mujo having a very chill comfortable vibe and Hiyakawa being more like a museum and culinary course. At Brush you get a more chill vibe and can get as little or as much information you want to the meal. I would also say that Brush is much less overbearing on the rules than either Mujo and Hiyakawa which was very nice. The quality of the fish and dishes were amazing. Brush has a unique rice and some unique presentations that the other places don't have. All things considered I think Brush my be the best overall place (accounting for price, comfort and experience). The only draw back of the omakase experience for me is the the space in not an intimate as the other spots I have mentioned. You can definitely tell you are in Buckhead.
The vibe here is so relaxing I nearly fell asleep meditating. Great eats, and even greater vibes and service. Highly recommend.

Probably more than the meal I enjoyed the customer service. They were freakishly kind for atlanta service standards. So personal, attentive, & warm‚Ä¶.which is probably the basis for my review. They have house made sauces, sandwich freebies, & vegan options. I wished the portions were larger and there was a sign on building because without it you‚Äôll certainly miss it. Overall do recommend

vision is one of my favorite places to be whether it‚Äôs for happy hour during the week or the party on the weekends. Food is 10/10! These 3 made us feel very important and filled our evening with their warm smiles and positive attitudes. The fresh ravioli seafood pasta inspired by Venice is what I really enjoyed. It was mouth watering. For dessert, the chocolate bombe, tiramisu and coffee copa ice cream were all so yummy. I can't wait to eat here again the next time I visit Atlanta.

One chance they get there's to many other great restaurants to try plus Im staying in mid-town Pricci was a long Uber ride and not worth the time we invested. The snapper was wonderful

Taqueria definition: a Mexican restaurant specializing in tacos. As a mexican, I felt out of place at this taqueria because it is NOT AUTHENTIC. This is basically a locally owned On the Border / La Frontera Grill. The food isn't the worst but far from flavorful. Even the cashier said, "Were a boring Taqueria" My husband hates these types of places because they profit/benefit from the name 'Taqueria' when the flavor/authenticity isn't there. It's cultural appropriation, but I'm sure it's okay since some of the workers were Hispanic, and 1 co-Founder is Mexican. But the main guy is Mike Klank, a white American. It saddens me that Mr. Hernandez has accepted to Americanize our Mexican culture for financial gain. It's altered to fit the demographic they're looking for. The same thing is happening in Mexico. I understand that, but its not right. Its white-washed. Health inspection was an 86 B. No onions or cilantro on the tacos. Tacos are made with flour tortillas, not corn. No salsa bar. Enchilada is $4 each, and it looked like vomit. The chicken it had was rotisserie chicken. Canned beer was $5 each. Guac was the only decent thing there. We took the food to go, adding a 5% fee. We went to El Rey del Taco right after for real Mexican food. Don't recommend and won't be back.

I love the food however I went in on a busy night and my husband was in line to order (3 spots away) and I‚Äôm pregnant so I found a table to sit at and was promptly told to leave the table until my order had been completed. I understand that may be the policy normally, but as I am very pregnant I would think MAYBE an exception could be made especially when my husband was 3 people away from ordering. So great food but really insensitive service.

I ordered the thai chicken fried rice with no onions and no tomatoes and it was perfect!! The rice was seasoned and sticky just how i like it. I didn‚Äôt even need to use duck or soy sauce as i always do. This is definitely a hidden gem and I‚Äôm glad i live 6 minutes away because i will definitely be coming back!

BEWARE OF THE SECRET RESERVATION LIST!! It is very well advertised that this is a ‚Äúno reservations taken‚Äù restaurant. We learned the hard way that you actually CAN make reservations (by emailing the owner directly). So, when we put our name in for a group of 4 at 6:30 pm and the hostess told us there were only 3 tables ahead of us, we were more than happy to wait as we had been wanting to try this spot for a long time. 2 hours after patiently waiting outdoors (you can‚Äôt wait indoors here), and after watching many groups stroll in to their RESERVED tables, we decided to check in with the hostess. Her advice was that we should have made a reservation by contacting the owner directly. So, if you find yourself waiting for a table here, just know that the empty table you see through the window may just remain empty until a limo full of people with a secret reservation arrives for their 8:15 reservation. Easy fix: instead of leading on to your customers that they are the third ones in line for a table, tell them the truth (we have some large parties tonight, special event or request, etc). If we knew the truth, we would have simply returned another night. Alas, our patience did not prevail and we gave up at the 2 hour mark.

And speaking of soggy, the French fries were limp as can be. They were listed on the menu as having black garlic and truffle, but truffle flavor (truffle salt?) was all I could taste. I did see some black specs, which I hoped and assumed were some sort of edible item, but otherwise the garlic was absent. Cafe Flora is an institution in Seattle. One of the first major vegetrian restaurants in the city. When my wife went to the wait staff inquiring when our food would be staff, a waitress said she would "check." Once the food arrived it was ordinary. Well and beautifully plated. But it was generally bland and boring. I don't blame the wait staff. Clearly management of the restaurant has left it understaffed. Our waitress was taking care of 15 tables in our room and disappeared for long periods. Perhaps serving even more tables elsewhere. A totally unpleasant experience. Oh and did I say it was my wife's birthday?? What a downer.

Everything we tried at The Harvest Vine tasted wonderful and was plated beautifully. This was the perfect restaurant for a birthday dinner with my parents :) we ordered a total of 8 dishes, including appetizers, mains, and dessert, to share among the 3 of us, and it was just the right amount. My favorite main dish was the Octopus, which was so soft and not rubbery at all! My favorite vegetable dish was the Spinach. The pine nuts and raisins pair so well with the natural bitterness of the spinach. We ordered 2 desserts, both of which were delicious, but if I had to pick just one to recommend, it‚Äôd be the Flan de Cafe. Everything we ordered (besides the bread) was gluten free, including the chocolate torte (flourless!). Great atmosphere and spectacular service! Looking forward to going back!

I have been coming to Cafe Lago since I was a student so many years ago. I moved on but I was smitten with the delicate raviolis then and they are still just as good 3 decades later. A ‚Äúmust visit‚Äù recommendation for any trip to Seattle. And sorry but after eating ravioli here, you will not want to get ravioli at any other restaurant. The grilled eggplant also highly recommended.

What can you say about a restaurant which has not lowered its standards in decades? Gnocchis which would float off your plate if they were not held down by a sublimely well balanced marinara. A lasagna as delicate as Thai silk...and I could go on and on. The service was discreet, smooth. A knowledgeable and friendly staff. The wine is well chosen and priced sensibly. Thank you Cafe Lago for still being part of the Seattle dining scene.

I lam ve the atmosphere of the place. The staff are so friendly. Food was good. I ordered a cold sandwich but i rather not order it again. It tasted good but i prefer a hot sandwich for lunch. The restaurant also close to donuts cafe. So we grabbed some donuts after lunch. I would recommend try this place at least once.

This is a real "locals" restaurant/bar. We were in Seattle over the Christmas holiday and hadn't booked any reservations for Christmas Eve dinner. So, my son did a little online research and found this Cafe had a special holiday menu that night, including a turkey, mashed potatoes & gravy, and cranberries! No reservations needed. We walked in and the "family" restaurant room was full, but we elected to sit in the bar. Great choice! The music was better, service was great and the food was really good (I did have the turkey special). It was a great mix of people too: race, gender, age, orientation...a fun melting pot of a real community. We had hot toddies with dinner and my daughter in law had a peppermint schnapps shake for dessert. It was s blast!

The perfect restaurant in town for picky eaters, families, college students, friend gatherings, and late-night freelancers (I've used the wifi here on my laptop and it works great! Power outlets are definitely much rarer though as it is much more of a restaurant than a cafe per se)

Pretty bad all across the board. I've given it a few chances and have continually been stunned by the poor quality of food and zombie-like servers. I always give the benefit of the doubt as I'm a restaurant "lifer," but suckage is suckage. And it's available at Lost Lake Cafe. JonJ

Cafe Con Leche provides serviceable Cuban food. The Con Leche sandwich has good flavor. Passeo Caribbean is about a half mile north on 1st and provides bigger messier sandwiches for about $2 more. Cafe Con Leche has a more sit down restaurant feel and better if you want quiet. Cafe Con Leche also has a big banquet hall with dance floor used for live bands and salsa lessons. Great place to drink with big groups or Latin music lovers alike...just be aware the food is second fiddle to the ambiance.

The record store is a one-of-a-kind and deserves 5 stars! Cafe review only - The restaurant menu provides many different variations of egg, sausage, vegetable, and potato dishes. We anticipated the quality of the cafe food to be similar to a IHOP, and we found it met that level of American-style breakfast dishes. The welcoming staff were friendly and offered to come find us when a table was ready so that we could peruse the record store in search of artistic gems. The combination of the record store and cafe is an excellent idea, however, a little more attention to the quality of a few select dishes, rather than offering a long listed of similar dishes, would help to elevate the status of the cafe among local foodies. Being from out-of-state, we were pleasantly surprised to find the local farmers' market right outside of Easy Street Records & Cafe, making that an enjoy morning experience overall on a Sunday morning.

Wow, so so glad we found Luna Park Cafe when we was visiting from England. This was exactly what we were looking for! A whole vegan menu, the food was absolutely delicious! Service was so good, really welcoming & friendly. The best food we ate whilst on our whole trip for sure‚Ä¶ We made sure we re visited before heading home and we really hope we will be back again in the future. If you‚Äôre looking for an awesome vegan breakfast, lunch or dinner with a cool setting inside the restaurant look no further! You‚Äôve got to try it out.
Can't get any fresher. Great place for seafood. Not quite a restaurant setting, more of a cafe. Good wine list as well
It has been a very long time since I ate a delicious pizza like this. All fresh ingredients and perfectly cooked. Not to mention that very generously added toppings!!! Go Sicilian Pizza go !!!!!!
Good pizza and wings!
Food was hot I ordered large sausage pepperoni green pepper extra cheese it was delicious and they actually added the extra cheese and they where open after 1 so I was definitely
The service was good. The selection is very good.
The chicken thigh was good until I got to the middle. It wasn't cooked fully. I hope I don't get sick. The rest of the food was good.
I should've read the reviews first... Small and tasteless. I'll leave it at that.
A little on the expensive side, but very tasty!
Fantastic small business find! Great prices, delicious food, and exceptional service. A true gem in the community!
The food was very tasty and they have a vegetarian option, which was great for me. Milagros, the host, was very welcoming.

The customer service was top tier. I was provided with quick service and a load of smiles. The waitress was very attentive and had an upbeat attitude towards work. I've never had Filipino food, so it was quite the experience to get out of my comfort zone. I was recommended a couple of items off of the menu so the product knowledge was on point. My food came with in a valid time not too late, and it was made with a chef's kiss.

Terrible waitress! Did not tell us about food and beer specials, starting clearing plates before everyone finished, not attentive, and we asked for the desert menu, she brought one for the table. Food was good, but not filling, deserts take 15-40 minutes. We Went around the corner for a pizza slice and desert.

Extremely unprofessional. They have the wrong phone number listed here. The number on this listing is for their F St. location. I called, asked for the hours, hurried over by car, only to find the restaurant closed with different hours. When I called back, the employee told me that I must've went to the wrong location because I called the F St location. She was quite amused at this..... how silly of me to assume that the number linked here was for this location I was coming to check it out after many recommendations since I was looking for a new go-to lunch spot but this left a very bad taste in my mouth

They are famous for the Chicago style deep dish pizza, even though there was no Chicago style deep dish pizza. The food was cold when we got it, and it was undercooked. There are also holes in the bathroom, which makes me feel very uncomfortable

The Food was decent, that is about my only compliment for this place. The service was some of the worst I have ever experienced, we went here with about 2 hours before our train arrived. Everything took comedically long, they took about fifty minutes to an hour to bring us food after we ordered, then didn't come back at all for another 40 minutes. Eventually, about 6 minutes before our train left they brought the check. We literally had to sprint to the platform like a scene from a movie. Thankfully we got to our train on time.

the papusas are very good but the prices online do not match the prices in store. No big deal. However, the chicken in the tacos was rather bland and parts of it were blue?? needless to say I only ate one

Our trip from NYC to Washington DC led us to Wendy's, but it wasn't what we expected. The service was super slow, and it felt like the staff weren't enjoying their work. Waiting for a sandwich took about 30 minutes, and when we finally got it, the food wasn't as good as we hoped, especially compared to other Wendy's we've been to. It was a surprise disappointment for us during our visit to DC.
Messed up my order and gave me a lettuce wrap on the verge of going bad I had to throw it out. Don‚Äôt order from here!

If you want something you have to call and ask first because they may or may not be able to make you what is on the menu. Do not have your heart set on anything it will just leave You disappointed. Do not believe the price that you see they change the price quite often constantly raising the food cost. The hours online are incorrect. I called to get food the other day. They said they weren‚Äôt available to service us until 4 o‚Äôclock but the establishments store hours are operating from 12 PM to 4 AM. Today I didn‚Äôt get an answer at all! They don‚Äôt answer the phone consistently If you get in contact with anybody at rotisserie chicken, you‚Äôre a lucky individual. I actually would not recommend this place to anyone because if you have to go through all of this to get food and it‚Äôs not good. Only Lord knows the rest ‚Ä¶ wanted to make this my number 1 Spot on Georgia Avenue because I work near by but it‚Äôs been constant disappointment after disappointment so I won‚Äôt be back good luck to anybody trying to get a decent plate.
Great restaurant! The staff are all really friendly and the vibe is great. The food is tasty and the prices are reasonable for what you get.
It is a cute, quaint little spot with a full bar and homemade Latin food. Had the Papusas and a Cerveza. Total $8.00.
Very nice and patient service. Excellent tasty food and very good price. I got a bowl of salad base with chicken and beef, plus kimchi and it's a great combo.
First time for me . Portions are larger than I thought. Love the options!

Korean Fast Food restaurant. Think Qdoba, Reti, or Chipotle - similar atmosphere. Choose your base - rice (white or purple), noodles, burrito, or salad. Choose your protein - spicy pork, beef (bulgogi style), chicken or tofu. Choose your vegetable toppings, then your sauces and extra toppings. We found the quality excellent. The service was great - the young man came out and explained the menu and the overall concept. I did the bulgogi and chicken with a ton of veggies covered with a nice ranch cilantro sauce. It‚Äôs kind of a nice fusion of latin, US, and Korean style foods mixed in a bowl. They do allow online ordering for pick up and they have a rewards program for frequent customers. This was a nice meal and welcome healthier variation of a common fast food style.
great food & service! prices and serving sizes are very reasonable.

So tasty, what a gem!! I ordered the CURRY LAKSA NOODLE Soup, pictured. It can be all plant based - I asked for mushrooms, spinach and broccoli to be added/substituted for the chicken, and with no hesitation they accommodated me! I'm so pleased with this Union Station fast casual option, located on the second level. If you take the stairs opposite the Amtrak ticket counter, you'll find it with big open air seating. This dish also includes tofu, vegetables, rice sticks & egg noodle combination in a coconut curry broth, with bean sprouts, fresh! green beans, and corn. Amazing, and spicy warm. They have non spicy foods, too. I'll upload the current menu.
What a lovely surprise it was, here at the top floor of Union Station. Fair prices, professional and quick service, and great, real food. The best food option in the station.
The food was great, the service was great, and the speed of said food was very fast.
The staff are helpful and efficient in busy Union Station, and the food is on par with the other locations.

Visit while waiting for Amtrak train. Ordered: Chicken Bites - good & fresh Hotdog - acceptable White & Red wine - guess both are OK for an Amtrak station. Kudos to them, trying to keep up with a lot of people, but you still may need to wait to place an order. Dining area consists of dining room and 2 seating outside areas inside Union station. Pricewise: 2 glasses of wine (actually cans, the wine is canned) with chicken bites to share plus tips is about $45.
Great tasting food at a solid price, with friendly service! Great drinks too The fries are a must

Sangria bar and grill has the best lemon drop ever! The vodka and lemon juice is very well balanced. Definitely the best I‚Äôve tried so far. I truly recommend this place to everyone I know even people that don‚Äôt live in DC. Food is great and the atmosphere is always pleasant.
Marvin was amazing, as was dinner and drinks. Tacos were so good I ordered a second plate.
Super cozy and diverse crowd.

Excellent neighborhood restaurant for home style comfort food always. Especially when you don't feel like cooking yourself or can't cook very well. Lack of parking is a problem but there is nothing they can do about that

H & chicken manager and some of the staff are abusive and disrespectful to black people working in that store and the owner is doing nothing about it. I witnessed the incident that happened yesterday the accused the black lady of stealing chocolate cake and said she is not listening to instructions and she is not hard working because of the manager wants to bring her little sister to work in the store
Nice and accommodating ownership of this Subway!

At Ice N' Slice we discovered a delightful twist on our pizza nights. Here, Ethiopian spices dance with traditional flavors, creating something truly unique. This place is more than a restaurant; it's where food becomes an adventure, and every visit feels like home. For anyone craving a new flavor or a cozy spot to dine, Slice N' Ice is the perfect find.
Nice change to the usual pizza
we enjoyed a tasty vegetarian chili bowl
Held a 40 person private dinner here and they did such a great job. Everyone loved the food and it was overall a very relaxing experience!
Fantastic duck and beef Wellington! Perfect service and a beautiful place. The best!! One of our favorite places in DC!!

Been going here for years, love the drinks and cheese plates lol, but good menu... I can never decide on what to eat... trout almondine was great, escargot...lamb rack, seafood stew, cheese late selections... All delicious
This is one of our go tos! The burritos are so big that I try to convince myself to only eat half at a time, but they‚Äôre also so good that I can never stop myself!!

The food was amazing! The muscles and octopus were cooked to perfection. The duck leg was packed with flavor without leaving you feeling heavy. The service was great. All staff had a positive up beat attitude that made you feel at ease. And their day room‚Ä¶just book the reservation. You‚Äôll be happy.
I ate with a large group (100 people) and we never received the garlic bread we pre paided for. Took forever to recieve food and it was cold. At least the servers were nice.

I feel my food was rushed cooked and wasn‚Äôt prepared right and this is why I ordered Nandocas Choice, it‚Äôs a chicken sandwich which is supposed to come with coleslaw on it, & they didn‚Äôt put any coleslaw on the sandwich, the sandwich was so dry even with the peri-peri sauce, it shocked me because I never headed it that way, this was a horrible eating experience, I couldn‚Äôt even enjoy my food. I guess it‚Äôs better when you eat in and you can catch the mistakes faster.

I usually don‚Äôt like writing reviews, but I‚Äôm so disappointed with my Uber Eats order from yesterday. When the wings arrived, they were incredibly small, despite ordering a dozen. They were so tiny.I wasted my money, I will never order from this store again.
Great food, good service, excellent atmosphere.
A nice spot to hang out and meet up with friends. But Definitely watch your Bill , we ordered during happy hour and still got charged the full amount, our waiter had to fix bill 2x
Great food, friendly staff. It was a bit loud, it's not an intimate setting, but great for the group vibes. Recommend the calamari it was awesome.
That half of jerk chicken is the best In the world.

So good, my family and I went back twice! We came here the night we landed, and came back again before the flight out. Great pizza, fantastic lasagna & pastas. Service was good, and the servers are very friendly. Atmosphere overall is great and you'll see various people from the DC area go in. I'd recommend this to anyone who likes Italian food
Won't spend my money there any longer. Give me someone else food and caught an attitude when I questioned them about it. I will take my business elsewhere. Check your food before you leave.

It's terribly unhealthy but I love it and you will too. Your next go to Chinese one stop shop. parking is impossible on this street so you have to do the DC thing and turn on your hazards and pick it up quick. They're really fast though so it's fine
Wonderful meal in a cool old fashioned DC political restaurant. Steak was good and the cocktails were well made.
This was the best restaurant I found in DC. Very convenient to the capital. Steak was amazing! I came back many times

I honestly cannot believe this place only has 4.2 stars (at time of review). Literally everything we ordered, which was almost everything, was amazing. The kale salad (can‚Äôt remember exactly the name) might have been the best thing on the menu, which is remarkable for a fried chicken restaurant. The ordering and payment system was convenient and everything came really quickly. The atmosphere inside is kind of like a retro diner
The food is so good. Location is tight. Sometimes hard to find parking.

Food is OK. Overpriced. Service is nonexistent. Punch your order on the tablet, and pray it actually appears. No staff interaction. Tables are sticky. Not sure if anything ever gets cleaned. No positives to report. Don't waste your money. I was on vacation.

The waitstaff is very nice. The atmosphere was awkwardly quiet. No music. Vagrants coming in off the street. Pupusas were good. I don‚Äôt recommend the seafood soup. Seafood isn‚Äôt fresh and it all tasted very fishy, in a bad way. The fajitas don‚Äôt have much flavor and only come with 3 small tortillas. Maybe if you know what to order it‚Äôs better.
Do not eat at this subway, they are using old spoiled vegetables. I ordered a veggie sandwich - disgusting. I emailed several times and no reply.
BS that it closes at 7
Amazing vegan food! The oyster bites were sooooo delicious
This was our second time going, and the food was amazing. Food is cooked to order, so be prepared for a little wait, but it's definitely worth it.

The food here was so great. After talking with the waiter, he suggested we order butter chicken as we are not accustomed to south Indian spice. It was spot on. The Naan is delicious! We shared the butter chicken entree; we would recommend ordering extra rice or Naan with it as the rice portion given is rather small. The butter chicken portion was enough for 2 people (we finished it).

We live near by this restaurant and decided to have a dinner. We travel and eat out lots. Also being a Hindu vegetarian can write lots about this place. This restaurant had many new dishes which we don‚Äôt find in other Indian restaurants in NOLA. It took real long for our order and the portions were very small. The menu is glorified and all necessary accomplishments not served with appetizers or meals. We order the Paruppu wada for $10. Two small pieces of hard wada served without any chutney. Please don‚Äôt order this appetizer as it was too dry and no taste at all. We also ordered the Gobi Manchurian was tiny portion and dry without main ingredients like garlic. The main reason of our visit was to try the Gutti Vankaya, a fancy name for the eggplant curry. The peanut based curry was great but eggplants were not cooked to the perfection. Literally we ate curry sauce with rice. This restaurant is located in the CBD and great for the tourists who don‚Äôt care about their money. I would not recommend this restaurant for locals.

The food was nice (I had the paneer tikka masala) however my friend ordered the punjabi chole with mild spice and it was the spiciest dish that I had in recent time. They said that they couldn‚Äôt do anything to fix that. Main issue was the rude waitress. We didn‚Äôt want to judge for no reason, but this lady was just rude. She rolled her eyes at customers, and did not answer to our complaints (she said just leave a bad review). When talking with the manager, the main issue was resolved, but the waitress came up and was rude to the manager as well. She argued back in a disrespectful manner. The atmosphere, minus her, was nice and I would go again when those two issues were fixed.
BEST Bullet naan and paneer tikka masala. One of the best authentic food I tried here. Will come again. Also try out other Indian restaurant close to this. Both are good
Good food, we enjoyed ourselves here.

Laid back place with outside tables. Burger, ordered medium rare, came out well done, and was under-seasoned. Veggie burger was also under-seasoned. Both came on soft, floppy bread that tasted good but made the sandwich hard to hold. Fries and salad were very good.
Crab pie was out of this world. Muffins and scramble are something else too. Everyone there was friendly great neighborhood place.

Absolutely great! Had the sample platter with a side of peas and rice. Easily enough for three people. Jerk shrimp, pork ribs, beef and chicken with plantains and cornbread. Another wonderful restaurant on the Point!

It was a busy time, so I get it. But our food took over an hour to get to us and not once in Between did the server check on us. Had a London fog for the first time, very tasty. The bearish breakfast was delicious. The potatoes are the truth!
We stopped in from wandering and had drinks here. Charming and interesting spot. Very interesting house cocktails! Fun garnishes!

Too loud, food took forever we left. Over priced drinks as well. Hard pass
Carre' was a great brunch choice for my birthday brunch. Everyone loved their food, the service was great. The drinks were delish and I will definitely be back.
Food was delicious

Had a 5:30pm reservation, didn‚Äôt get our appetizer until a half hour later, sat for an hour and and a half without our third appetizer, or entrees, had to leave due to another commitment never thinking a dinner would consume two hours of our evening. Can I just say "WOW"?! We booked a private dining experience in the Dauphine room for my cousin's bachelorette, it was such a beautiful intimate atmosphere. The service was lovely (shoutout to Allen!) and the food was fantastic. We even got a surprise visit from the Easter Bunny! 1000000/10!
Good changes..in decor. Nice place, we like it. Foodie 2 adores the vindaloo.
Server forgot to ask one guest in our party if they wanted desert.
Despite it's touristy location, they ensure you feel like a local. Jazz brunch for the win! Crawfish and goat cheese crepe, with a mimosa.

Very good steak, pretty good egg/fried oyster appetizer and Caesar salad. Food a little salty. Very good red wine selection. Felt a little awkward dining there by myself. Waiter wasn't paying full attention; he took the drink menu after I had asked him to leave it with me.

I love everything about this place. The food is always great and the atmosphere just feels right. Dine outside and you will be surrounded by some of the beauty ad architecture that the city has to offer.
Less crowded than most places. Food was delicious.

I ended up here after a long day of touristing. My travel companion became ill and I made spontaneous plans at 9 at night for dinner. Whomever is in the kitchen is directly from heaven. I had a very odd pairing of the cauliflower and wine pub burger and, I‚Äôve never had anything so delicious! It was paired with a Savage wine , Senso. The pairing was amazing. The people who work here or I should say who are performing artistry here know what they‚Äôre doing. This place is inviting, chill and cozy. Delicious food! Amazing staff!
Amazing food, great service, and the perfect music selection!
This was my 2020 staple and is still my favorite comfort food to this day

We were fortunate to get a recommendation to this hidden gem on Frenchman from a local artist. There is literally about ten tables, and they don't take reservations, so it's recommended to get there when they open. For an appetizer, we ordered the mussels. They were delicious! Good food and good service! So good we can for breakfast and back for lunch the next day.

Food was great! Got the shrimp and grits and oyster benedict. Very slow service and the hostess was not pleasant, at all. There were several tables that were seated before us and we finished our food and left and they still didn't get their food. The staff was not apologetic to the customers and almost acted annoyed at them.

I‚Äôve had their food 50+ times and it never disappoints!!! The food is made quickly, the service is wonderful, and they are family owned. I love supporting them and I hope they stay in their CBD location forever
This is some legitimately fantastic Thai food with the added bonus of some top-class cocktails. Spice and flavor were perfect, as is the ambiance. Will definitely return!

Came in on an early Friday evening after walking around all afternoon with a drink in my hand. . Was pretty empty, sat at the bar by my lonesome and ordered food before the drive home. It was so good. Staff incredibly friendly as well. No alcohol, but still tipped 20%.
Great place
The food and service were excellent.

This place was okay. The food wasn't bad, however it also wasn't anything spectacular. Prices were okay. I drawn by the Friday crab cake lunch special on the menu, but they were out. Let's start with the first class service they give you from the minute you arrive you are treated like a VIP. The food is absolutely delicious and the Binets are out of this world!

This place is very accommodating, friendly and warm. Alexander was our helper and he was the best- so is Roy. We had a family post graduation dinner here and it is unforgettable. Lisa is excellent! She is very personable and fun! Thank you!
Great breakfast. Lisa was an excellent, friendly server. Everything came quick and prepared perfectly. Best biscuit I have had in a while.

Husband had shrimp and grits very good wife had very disappoint biscuits and sausage gravy it was a lie It was a plain sawmill gravy with chopped up sausage patties kind of gross so shrimp and grits one of she best in town happy wife happy life in if you eat here ü•Ç 28 year wedding anniversary Trip. Update before we left look at my coffee and grounds are floating in it

Pamela was absolutely fabulous and so kind. She happily made us drinks to go
Awesome food and service!

Wasn't too busy at the time we went, although reservations are available if needed. Server was informative and friendly. Alligator was good, not chewy or fishy. Ceasar salad was large and romaine was beautifully fresh. Shrimp cocktail was ok, a bit sweet for my taste but liked that it did not have raw chunky tomatoes. Our waiter was attentive and the food was DELICIOUS! Wasn‚Äôt offered any dessert, though, which was off. But HIGHLY recommend!
Very slow personnel... not friendly at all...
Stay away very rude staff. Acted like the smallest issue was the biggest deal in the world. You really have to try to be as rude as they were.
No word needed. This is what I got for my steak and cheese sandwich. In addition to this, they don't open their bathroom for customers either.

Located in the heart of Lakeview, Russell‚Äôs Marina Diner stands as a cherished beacon of New Orleans‚Äô rich culinary tradition. Since its inception in 1985, this diner has carved out a niche for itself as the go-to destination for exceptional breakfasts, weaving itself into the fabric of the city‚Äôs dining scene. With a menu that spans the gamut from indulgent fried chicken and waffles to a diverse array of egg specialties, Russell‚Äôs caters to a broad spectrum of tastes. Not forgetting the health-conscious, the diner also offers lighter fare such as eggwhite omelets and sweet potato pancakes, ensuring that every patron leaves satisfied. The dining experience is further enhanced by the option to enjoy your meal either inside the diner‚Äôs cozy interior, at the counter where the local vibe thrives, in their inviting dining room, or outside on the pet-friendly patio, making it perfect for every occasion. During my visit, I decided to try the legendary Egg Saints #33‚Äîa daring concoction that perfectly embodies New Orleans‚Äô flair for culinary innovation. This dish features a grilled biscuit topped with alligator sausage, grilled tomatoes, poached eggs, and smothered in homemade country gravy. Each component of the dish harmonizes to create a breakfast experience that is both unique and profoundly satisfying. From the moment I stepped inside, I was greeted with the diner‚Äôs unmistakable local charm, enhanced by the friendly service that made me feel right at home. The ambiance, a blend of the cozy and the communal, set the perfect stage for what was to be an unforgettable meal. The Premier League playing softly in the background added a touch of camaraderie, reminiscent of a neighborhood caf√© where everyone is welcome. The highlight of my visit was, without a doubt, the food. The Egg Saints #33 was a revelation, transforming the classic eggs Benedict into a dish that captivated my palate and left me pondering the culinary prowess behind it. Every bite was a testament to Russell‚Äôs commitment to quality and innovation, making it clear why this diner holds a special place in the hearts of New Orleans‚Äô residents and visitors alike. In a city lauded for its vibrant food scene, claiming the title of "best breakfast" is no small feat. Yet, as I left Russell‚Äôs Marina Diner, I was already yearning to return and dive deeper into their menu. This hidden gem is an absolute must-visit for anyone looking to experience the soul of New Orleans through its food, served with a side of unmatched hospitality.
